div.p: Access byte bit-field and concrete hex values for Global Descriptor Table
Flat Memory Model: All code/data segments use Base = 0x00000000 and Limit = 0xFFFFFFFF so that logical address = linear address. Isolation is enforced via paging (CR3), not via segment base/limit.
